Happy #NegroniWeek!⁠
⁠
Join us in New York, Denver, and Los Angeles through the weekend for Negronis for a good cause, supporting the incredible work of @anotherroundanotherrally and @rwcfusa. Can't make it to the bar? There's never a better time to make a Negroni at home. Try our White Negroni as an end-of-season toast with the recipe below. (📸: @dylanandjeni)⁠
⁠
1.5 oz London dry gin⁠
1 oz blanc vermouth⁠
0.75 oz Suze⁠
Garnish: 1 orange twist⁠
Stir all the ingredients over ice, then strain into an Old-Fashioned glass over 1 large ice cube. Express the orange twist over the drink, then gently rub it around the rim of the glass and place it into the drink.⁠
⁠
For more on @imbibe's #NegroniWeek, head to the link in our bio. Enjoy!

One of our favorite reviews of D&C Denver's Outrigger? "Made this at home many times, and no one has ever sent it back." Whiskey fans with a penchant for passion fruit, this one is for you. Give it a try it at home — and make an extra to put it to the aforementioned test — with @jonnyfoursquare's recipe below. (📸: @shawnxcampbell)⁠
⁠
1 oz Wyoming Whiskey ⁠
0.75 oz Old Grand Dad 114⁠
0.25 Yellow Chartreuse ⁠
1 Teaspoon Giffard Passion Fruit⁠
1 Teaspoon Vanilla Syrup ⁠
3 Dashes Orange Bitters ⁠
1 Dash Bitter Truth Aromatic ⁠
Method: Stir ⁠
Glassware: SOF / Large Rock⁠
Garnish: Orange Twist

node.text:
A riff on the Vesper, @apday's Little Victory features an aromatized wine (Cocchi Americano bianco) flavored with a few drops of root beer extract. On its own, the infused Cocchi is tasty, but when mixed into the cocktail it gets a little lost, so we add a bit of orange marmalade, which introduces a touch of sweetness and a pleasant bitterness that bridges the flavors and helps highlight the infused Cocchi. Make it at home with the recipe below. (📸: @dylanandjeni)⁠
⁠
1.5 oz dry gin⁠
0.5 oz vodka⁠
1 oz Root Beer–Infused Cocchi Americano (1 bottle Cocchi Americano Bianco and 2.75 grams Terra Spice root beer extract, combined and refrigerated) ⁠
1 tsp orange marmalade⁠
Garnish: 1 orange wedge⁠
⁠
Stir all the ingredients over ice, then double strain into a double Old-Fashioned glass over 1 large ice cube. Garnish with the orange wedge. Cheers!

Introducing our Death & Co x @amass.botanics Natural Tobacco candle. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
A sip of a drink, a nostalgic song, a burning candle — all intimate moments that can instantly take you back to a memory. In honor of these sensory experiences, we teamed up with our friends at AMASS to create a signature Death & Co scent, designed to transport you to an evening at the bar.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Our Natural Tobacco fragrance is now available in a soy wax candle. Crafted with @amass.botanics' signature quality and care, the candle features warm notes of lavender, vanilla, juniper, and bergamot. It's natural soy, vegan, cruelty-free, and has an estimated burn time of over 60 hours — meaning significantly extended enjoyment. Shop the D&C Market exclusive now through the link in our bio.

Interested in joining the Death & Co team? NYC is in search of a bartender and we want to hear from you.⁠

More than a static list of required qualifications and responsibilities, our application process includes insight into what we value, what we strive to offer our staff and our guests, and what makes us proud to come to work every day. Getting to know you beyond your resume is important to us both in the process and behind the bar.⁠
⁠
If you’re interested in applying for a bartending position at D&C NYC, head to the link in our bio. (📸: @ericmedsker)

node.text:
Apples play three parts in D&C LA's Menagerie, created by @matthewsbelanger. ⁠
⁠
Find them first in Montreuil Calvados, a collaboration between legendary importer Charles Neal and veteran calvados producer Patrice Giard. The project uses apples from Giard's orchards in the Pays d'Auge, fermented and then distilled twice using a traditional Alembic still. Next, Leopold Sour Apple Liqueur features a blend of New York state apples macerated in spirit. Finally, a Granny Smith apple garnish gives a final visual performance. Try it on your next visit to D&C LA. (📸: @meetjakob)
